    public static class SmallProgressMeasureSolver.ProgressMeasure
extends java.util.HashMap<GameState,SmallProgressMeasureSolver.Tuple>
    A progress measure is a map from a state to its tuple. A progress measure pm1 is smaller than or equal to another progress measure pm2 is for every state s, pm1(s) ≤ pm2(s).
    Author:
    Ming-Hsien Tsai

      • ProgressMeasure

        public ProgressMeasure(Game game,
                       StateSet subgame,
                       GamePlayer player)
        Initializes this progress measure for a subgame of a parity game. All tuples are (0, 0, ..., 0) after initialization.
        Parameters:
        game - a parity game
        subgame - the states of the subgame
        player - the game player which the solver is going to solve the parity game for
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the game is not a parity game
